summary:
In 2019 I successfully completed my Bachelor's Degree in Archaeology from the University of Padova Italy. My thesis on ancient numismatics, provided me with an interest in the Mediterranean region.
Im currently following my masters studies at the University of Leiden in the Applied Archaeology program. 
During my studies and after graduation I was given the opportunity to participate in excavations at Ancient Eleutherna in Crete for five consecutive summers, working on various sites such as the Necropolis that verified and confirmed my willingness to pursue this field of study.
Recently I had also the opportunity to work on my first rescue archaeological project in the city of Athens at the port of Piraeus.
Working on such an interesting site gave me the opportunity to practice the theory,
to pay attention to details, to be patient and to work with people from different cultures as
a team.
Listening to a variety of view points along with a wide range of personal and
professional experience offered me new perspective and inspired me.
